<TD valign=top><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" COLOR="#333399"><b>Zyla</b></FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399"><B>Apprentice</B></font><BR><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Joined: Jun 13, 2001</FONT><br><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Posts: 13</FONT></td><TD valign="top"><img src="/boards/images/posticon.gif"><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Posted: 2001-06-21 02:12&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp<HR></font>

<FONT COLOR="#333399" face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">I've done this quest a few times.  Once for myself and then for my friends.<BR><BR>1st off, go to Crystal Caverns and get a bottle of acid that drops randomly off of the orcs.  You don't have to have the item from the Queen.  On my server, you can't even get to the queen because there's always a necro or a wizard sitting there camping.  But hey, while you're there, you can get some other items by killing the named mobs too if they're not camped.  The acid is no-drop and many people will let you come loot it if you tell them that you're looking for it.  Just be sure not to train them on your way there <IMG SRC="/boards/images/smiles/icon_wink.gif"><BR><BR>Next, go to the wiz spires in GD and kill dire wolves until the Bloodwolf spawns.  You will also need to kill plenty of giants as well because you have to be kindly considerate or higher to get the quest to work.  I think I read somewhere that they changed it so that you have to be an ally, but I could be wrong.  Anyway, kill the BW and loot the BW Harness, then head to Thurgadin.<BR><BR>Talk to Erdarf Restil in the bar across from the Cleric Zone.  Ask him, "What user of Priestly magic?"  If he continues to talk with you, you have enough faction.  If not, you must continue to kill giants/dire wolves until he will let you talk with him further.  Give him the acid and he will give you a gem of persuasion.<BR><BR>Next, take the gem and the bloodwolf harness and trot along invis through the wurm cave to the other side from Thurgadin (be careful because some wurms can see thru invis and they are random).  To the right there will be a small hut where Vores the Hunter stays.  Give him the bloodwolf harness and the gem and he will give you a Harness of Control.<BR><BR>Now comes the strategic part.  The best way I have done it is to have a 2 person group (myself and a bard).  I bound myself on the side of the fort and then went down to camp the broodmother while the bard waited up top for the giants to run out.  When the BM spawned, I gave her the harness, then gated to the castle.  The bard watched her after she walked out of the tunnel so that nobody could run off with her.  I did it this way to avoid aggroing other wurms onto us as some can see thru invis (see above).<BR><BR>  Once the BM got to the fort, she kept the one giant busy while Frostsky ran out.  The bard nabbed Frostsky and kited him around while I snared/dotted/nuked and then I got my leggings.  Note to all who try this alone:  Frostsky has 10k+ hp's and hits pretty hard, so be very very careful not to aggro anything else other than him or you might end up having to redo the whole quest over.<BR><BR>I still remember how pumped up I was when I got the leggings.  They are well worth it, not to mention the graphics look very cool on a female wood elf.<BR><BR>Hope it helps <IMG SRC="/boards/images/smiles/icon_smile.gif">
